data.name: symAreaRepeatY.ToolTip
data.value: The vertical separation between symbols, in mm. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaOriginY.ToolTip
data.value: The y-coordinate of the symbol grid origin, in mm. Only applies if OriginControl evaluates to Global or Local. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaAngle.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the angle of each repeating symbol, in degrees. Only applies if AngleControl evaluates to FromAngle. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaOriginControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies how the symbol grid origin is defined. This must evaluate to one of: Global (default), Local, or Centroid

data.name: symAreaBufferWidth.ToolTip
data.value: The width, in mm, of the buffer zone relative to the polygon boundary in which the symbol is rendered. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaRepeatX.ToolTip
data.value: The horizontal separation between symbols, in mm. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaOriginX.ToolTip
data.value: The x-coordinate of the symbol grid origin, in mm. Only applies if OriginControl evaluates to Global or Local. Defaults to 0

data.name: symAreaClippingControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the clipping behavior of the symbol at polygon boundaries. This must evaluate to one of: Clip (default), Inside, or Overlap

data.name: symAreaAngleControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies how the symbol angle is defined. This must evaluate to one of: FromAngle (default) or FromGeometry

data.name: symLineVertexMiterLimit.ToolTip
data.value: The limit to use when drawing miter vertex joins. A miter vertex join is trimmed if the ratio of the miter length to symbol height is greater than the miter limit. If specified this must be greater than zero. Defaults to 5

data.name: symLineVertexAngleLimit.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the limiting angle, in degrees, by a which the feature geometry can change before some of the VertexControl options take effect. If specified this must be greater than or equal to zero. Defaults to 0

data.name: symLineEndOffset.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies where the symbol distribution ends, relative to the end of the feature. Defaults to 0

data.name: symLineAngle.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the symbol angle, in degrees. Only applies if AngleControl evaluates to FromAngle. Defaults to 0

data.name: symLineUnitsControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies whether the distribution parameters are interpreted as absolute values (in mm) or parametric values. This must evaluate to one of: Absolute (default) or Parametric

data.name: symLineVertexJoin.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the wrapping behavior at vertices for all graphic elements. Only applies if VertexControl evaluates to OverlapWrap. This must evaluate to one of: None, Bevel, Round (default), or Miter

data.name: symLineRepeat.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the separation between repeating symbols. Defaults to 0

data.name: symLineStartOffset.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies where the symbol distribution begins, relative to the start of the feature. Defaults to 0

data.name: symLineVertexControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the symbol behavior at vertices. This must evaluate to one of: OverlapNone (default), OverlapDirect, OverlapNoWrap, or OverlapWrap

data.name: symLineAngleControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies how the symbol angle is defined. This must evaluate to one of: FromAngle or FromGeometry (default)

data.name: textBox16.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the default path attributes to use when drawing the symbol. These apply to any centerline that gets drawn where the symbol can't draw, and to path elements that don't specify attributes. The geometry contained in this path is ignored and should be empty

data.name: symPointOriginOffsetY.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the vertical offset to apply to the symbol origin, in mm. This offset is applied before the symbol is scaled and rotated. Defaults to 0

data.name: symPointAngle.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the symbol angle, in degrees. Only applies if AngleControl evaluates to FromAngle. Defaults to 0

data.name: symPointOriginOffsetX.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies the horizontal offset to apply to the symbol origin, in mm. This offset is applied before the symbol is scaled and rotated. Defaults to 0

data.name: symPointAngleControl.ToolTip
data.value: Specifies how the symbol angle is defined. This must evaluate to on of: FromAngle (default), or FromGeometry

data.name: chkArea.ToolTip
data.value: Check to allow this Symbol Definition to be used in the context of polygons

data.name: chkLine.ToolTip
data.value: Check to allow this Symbol Definition to be used in the context of lines

data.name: chkPoint.ToolTip
data.value: Check to allow this Symbol Definition to be used in the context of points
